      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GOLDIE RUSTY (1) was prominent early from the tricky draw and stalked the lead before levelling up to score (19.98) at Angle Park in a Grade 5 over 342m. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from five starts. The hardest to beat again. ADHANA ROY (2) turned in a better effort at Angle Park last start, finishing third behind No Ear Trindall (20.21) in a Grade 6. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. The form out of last race has been strong. Expected to feature again. BOUNDING HOME (8) drew an outside box and was game in defeat when only 1.3 lengths from the winner Master Kilcoy in third(23.22) at this track. Hard to beat again. ONCE A DIVA (5) is hard to fault of late and is a strong top-three hope again.",
